race.comment: LOWESTOFT (11) eye-catching return over the shorter trip when a slashing third over 1203m at Kyneton. Gets in light with Pozman's 2kg claim and finds a very winnable race. Hard to stop. WRENLEE (8) raced a touch closer from the better draw when a plugging third over 1106m at this track in the soft (6) conditions. A repeat effort keeps him in the calculations. MIKE'S HOPE (5) Alabama Express three-year-old gelding out of the good producing mare Reglisse. Won all three of his recent jump outs in excellent style and clearly has a stack of ability. Gets in light with the claim but not too sure where he ends up from the draw. Could earn a trip to the Gold Coast if he aims up. PACIFIC REEL (6) far from disgraced on debut when he pulled up lame to finish seventh last start over 1415m at this course. Kept safe in betting on that occasion and expect a better showing here.
